VL  - 56
IS  - 3
SP  - 341
EP  - 355
PY  - 1993
DA  - 1993/04/01/
SN  - 0304-4076
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-4076(93)90125-O
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/030440769390125O
AB  - A pseudo-R2 measure for limited and qualitative dependent variable models is proposed. A consistent estimator of the variance of the disturbance term is also suggested. The pseudo-R2 measure is shown to have the same asymptotic limit as the conventional R2. The measure is adapted to the logit model in an empirical example of female car-ownership modeling. The pseudo-R2 is applicable to a wide set of limited and qualitative dependent variable models and offers a valuable tool for model evaluation.
