DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-4076(93)90129-S
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/030440769390129S
AB  - We show that negative definiteness of the Hessian matrix of the log likelihood is preserved at any stationary point under any one-to-one and onto parameter transformation which is differentiable. This rules out the possibility, suggested by Greene (1990), of multiple roots of the likelihood equations for the Tobit as well as the truncated regression models.
